title: Idaho ties in the NFL (2015 Week 5): Buccaneers’ Martin scores three TDs; Bears’ McClellin gets hurt
text:
Order a reprint of this story 
Tampa Bay Buccaneers running back Doug Martin (22) flips over Jacksonville Jaguars defensive end Jared Odrick (75) after scoring on a 1-yard touchdown run during the fourth quarter of an NFL football game Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015, in Tampa, Fla PHELAN M. EBENHACK — The Associated Press 
Heres a look at how NFL players from Idaho high schools and colleges fared during Week 5 of the 2015 NFL season: 
SUNDAY 
• Tampa Bay RB Doug Martin (No. 22, Boise State) had 24 carries for 123 yards and two 1-yard touchdowns against Jacksonville. He also had three catches for 35 yards, including a 10-yard TD. 
• Chicago ILB Shea McClellin (No. 50, Marsing High/Boise State) started at Kansas City and made five tackles before injuring his left knee on the first play of the second half. LT Charles Leno Jr. (No. 72, Boise State) also started for the Bears. 
• Dallas DT Tyrone Crawford (No. 98, Boise State) started against New England and had four tackles, including his second sack of the year. DE DeMarcus Lawrence (No. 90, Boise State) also started and made one stop. 
• Cincinnati SS George Iloka (No. 43, Boise State) started against Seattle and had four tackles and a pass deflection. 
• New Orleans CB Kyle Wilson (No. 24, Boise State) made two tackles at Philadelphia before leaving with an apparent leg injury. TE Josh Hill (No. 89, Blackfoot High/Idaho State) was targeted once on an incomplete pass. 
• Denver C Matt Paradis (No. 61, Council High/Boise State) started at Oakland. Raiders DE Benson Mayowa (No. 95, Idaho) made his season debut and had one tackle. 
• Arizona LG Mike Iupati (No. 76, Idaho) started at Detroit. 
• Washington DB Jeron Johnson (No. 20, Boise State) made one tackle at Atlanta. 
THURSDAY 
• Indianapolis DT Billy Winn (No. 99, Boise State) had two tackles at Houston. RG Hugh Thornton (No. 69, Mountain View High) started for the Colts.
